title: Bug 118780 - Column alias not displaying correctly in expression builder when selecting dataset
OB: When selecting the dataset in the expression builder and double-clicking on the first column name:
EB: According to scr 78193 in tracker, the first column in the expression builder should use the alias name instead of the original name. However, the original name of the first column is listed below the expression builder, and the alias name appears above as row["column1"] after double-clicking the original name.
SR:
1. Open the expression builder.
2. Select the dataset.
3. Double-click on the first column name.
4. Verify that the original name of the column is listed below the expression builder, and the alias name appears above as row["column1"].
